## Review Rules

1. Judge accuracy against the page image first and OCR second.
2. Ensure the tree captures all visible text and all relevant extracted images.
3. Ensure reading order is correct for columns, sidebars, tables, and mixed text-image layouts.
4. Ensure container nodes are used only for grouping and leaf nodes contain actual text or image references.
5. Ensure text is not missing, duplicated, or assigned to the wrong semantic type.
6. Ensure page-spanning, content-bearing artwork uses `full_bleed_image`, while purely decorative backdrops use `background_image`.
7. Ensure image nodes use only these IDs: {% if image_ids.size > 0 %}{% for id in image_ids %}{{ id }}{% unless forloop.last %}, {% endunless %}{% endfor %}{% else %}(none){% endif %}.
8. If the current structure is already accurate, set `approved` to `true`.
9. If there are meaningful issues, set `approved` to `false` and return a fully corrected replacement tree.
10. Always return a complete `nodes` array, even when `approved` is `true`.
11. Keep `reasoning` concise and specific about why the structure is correct or what was fixed.
